entry.value: create table IF NOT EXISTS ${tablename_tr:prepend('raw_db.')} as ${sql_create_table}
select ru_translit(tablename) as tablename_tr,tablename, tabletype from msk1_tablenames where tabletype in ('p_EntityType','p_ComplexType')
create table IF NOT EXISTS ${tablename_tr:prepend('core_db.')} as ${sql_create_table_t}

select 'select ' || string_agg('null::' || propertytype ||' as ' || propertyname , ', ') as pre_sql , 'select ' || string_agg('null::' || propertytype_t ||' as ' || propertyname , ', ') as pre_sql_t from ( select distinct propertyname as propertyname , case propertytype when 'Edm.Binary' then 'bytea' else 'text' end as propertytype , case propertytype when 'Edm.Binary' then 'bytea' when 'Edm.Boolean' then 'bool' when 'Edm.DateTime' then 'timestamp' when 'Edm.Double' then 'NUMERIC(16, 4)' when 'Edm.Int16' then 'integer' when 'Edm.Int64' then 'bigint' else 'text' end as propertytype_t from msk1_metadata where tablename = '${tablename}' order by propertyname ) as q

entry.value: select relname FROM ( SELECT pg_catalog.pg_namespace.nspname AS schema_name, relname, pg_relation_size(pg_catalog.pg_class.oid) AS table_size FROM pg_catalog.pg_class JOIN pg_catalog.pg_namespace ON relnamespace = pg_catalog.pg_namespace.oid ) t WHERE schema_name = 'raw_db' and table_size > 8192;
select string_agg(propertyref,',') as propertyref , ru_translit(tablename) as tablename_tr,tablename from msk1_propertyref mp group by tablename
select substring(ru_translit(tablename),'(^.*)_\w*$') as tablename_tr,tablename, 'fk_' || ru_translit(tablename) as fk from msk1_tablenames where tabletype in ('p_Association')

select substring(tablename,'.*_(.*)$')||'_key' as property, substring(ru_translit(association),'.*\.(.*)$') as association from msk1_associations ma where tablename = '${tablename}' and "role" = 'End';
